article_title: Lesser Prairie Chicken Survives a Scare in the Senate
article_text:
WASHINGTON—Strutting, proud, and given to noisy, chest-puffing displays, Plains-states legislators in the U.S. Senate on Wednesday considered the fate of the Lesser Prairie Chicken, one of their most controversial constituents.

While it’s become more scarce out West, the threatened Lesser Prairie Chicken has been popping up all over Capitol Hilland Republicans have declared open season. Several legislators from the bird’s home turf have been trying to remove the Lesser Prairie Chicken from the government’s official list...
